OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 28 Mar to Mon 6 AprFA
OL,6,Fbroadly changeable pattern will
OL,7,Fcontinue, at least through the first
OL,8,Fpart of this period, as further
OL,9,Ffrontal systems move across the UK,
OL,10,Fbringing rain and stronger winds at
OL,11,Ftimes. Weather fronts are likely to be
OL,12,Fmore active across northern areas,
OL,13,Fthus the wettest and windiest
OL,14,Fconditions are more likely here. As
OL,15,Fthey come south, often running in to a
OL,16,Fridge of higher pressure extending
OL,17,Ffrom the southwest, frontal systems
OL,18,Fwill often be weaker and rainfall
OL,19,Famounts smaller. In this setup,
OL,20,Ftemperatures will probably pan out
OL,21,Fclose to average overall, with some
OL,22,Fovernight frost where skies are clear
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fand winds light.
